Deanna Grounds resided at in 2014 in Gainesville, TX. Parents: George Gifford Grounds and Alice L. Corbett.

Ginny Grounds resided at in 2014 in Gainesville, TX. Parents: George Gifford Grounds and Alice L. Corbett. Eleanor May Grover was born on 9 Jul 1929 in Middleborough, MA. She died on 12 Jan 2007 in Rutland, Vermont.

She was married to Rev. Allan Packer Davis on 17 Jun 1950 in Brookville, MA. Children were: Rev. Glenn Allan Davis, Kathleen Joy Davis, Martha Jean Davis, Scott Nelson Davis.

Hannah Carpenter Grunvald was born on 13 Sep 1993 in Burlington, Vermont. Parents: Lloyd Stewart Grunvald and Julie Louise CARPENTER. Lloyd Stewart Grunvald was born on 11 Oct 1961 in Montreal, Canada.

He was married to Julie Louise CARPENTER on 29 Jul 1990 in Stowe, Vermont. Children were: Miles William Grunvald, Hannah Carpenter Grunvald, Warren Alexander Grunvald.

Miles William Grunvald was born on 15 Jan 1992 in Burlington, Vermont. As a pre-schooler, Miles enjoyed fishing with his grampa, and managed to catch a seagull in the fall of 1995. He also started playing hockey at that time. Miles, Hannah, and many of their cousins enjoyed eating maple syrup made on the farm that had once belonged to their great-great-great grandfather, George N. Carpenter, a civil war veteran. Parents: Lloyd Stewart Grunvald and Julie Louise CARPENTER. Warren Alexander Grunvald was born on 23 May 1995 in Burlington, Vermont. Parents: Lloyd Stewart Grunvald and Julie Louise CARPENTER. Dinah HAGAR was born before 5 May 1728. She was baptized on 5 May 1728. She died on 19 Jan 1792 in Paxton, Massachusetts. Parents: William Hagar and Mary FLAGG.

She was married to Abijah BEMIS on 29 Jan 1750. Children were: Abijah BEMIS, Daniel BEMIS Sr., Dinah BEMIS, Beulah BEMIS, Lydia BEMIS, John BEMIS, Ruth BEMIS, Alpheus BEMIS.

Elizabeth Hagar was born about 1854 in Massachussetts. The presence of Elizabeth as a daughter in this family is suggested by the 1860 federal census of Brighton, MA. However, Margaret would have been 51 when Elizabeth was born, so it is a strong possibility that Elizabeth is not a daughter, but otherwise related. Parents: Horatio Hagar and Margaret Ann Whitney. Ellen F. Hagar was born about 1842. Parents: Horatio Hagar and Margaret Ann Whitney. Horatio Hagar was born in 1801. He died in 1866. Horatio's occupation is listed as gardener in the 1860 census of Brighton, MA.

He was married to Margaret Ann Whitney on 1 Oct 1839 in Watertown, Massachusetts. Children were: Ellen F. Hagar, Sarah Louise Hagar, Elizabeth Hagar.

Sarah Louise Hagar was born about 1845. She died in 1869. Parents: Horatio Hagar and Margaret Ann Whitney. William Hagar Parents: William Hagar and Sarah Benjamin.

Children were: Dinah HAGAR.
